## AI-DLC Workflow

AI-DLC (AI-Driven Development Life Cycle) is active in this workspace.

At the start of every new task or conversation, ask:
> "AI-DLC is set up. Would you like to use the AI-DLC workflow for this task?"

If **no** — proceed normally.

If **yes**:
1. Detect workspace type: greenfield (no source files) or brownfield (existing code).
2. Present the appropriate phase list.
3. Ask which phase to start from.
4. Silently scan for prior artifacts (aidlc-docs/, docs/, README.md, etc.).
5. Summarise findings, then execute the chosen phase.

Ask only once per conversation.

### Greenfield Phases
1. Requirements analysis and validation
2. User story creation
3. Application Design
4. Parallel work units / task breakdown
5. Risk assessment and complexity evaluation
6. Detailed component design
7. Code generation and implementation
8. Build configuration and testing strategies
9. Quality assurance and validation
10. Deployment automation and infrastructure
11. Monitoring and observability setup
12. Production readiness validation

### Brownfield Phases (add Reverse Engineering as phase 0)
0. Reverse Engineering — analyse existing codebase
1–12. Same as greenfield above
